<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,365,551]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Newly recorded on Prince Edward Island and in the Maritime Provinces as a whole (
<figureCitation box="[1191,1277,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="28.[151,255,1653,1677]" captionTargetBox="[198,1406,626,1593]" captionTargetId="figure-175@28.[162,1425,607,1627]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distribution of Ptilinus pruinosus Casey, Ptilinus ruficornis Say, Lasioderma serricorne (Fabricius), Euvrilletta peltata (Harris), Vrilletta laurentina Fall, and Xyletinus fucatus LeConte in the Maritime Provinces of Canada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096679/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Widely distributed in the eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[445,504,445,471]" name="United States of America" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="White, R. E." box="[527,679,445,471]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="529 - 70" refId="ref23969" refString="White, R. E. (1982) A catalogue of the Coleoptera of America north of Mexico, Family Anobiidae. United States Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service, Agricultural Handbook 529 - 70." type="book chapter" year="1982">White 1982</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[747,835,445,471]" name="Canada" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Canada</collectingCountry>
recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[1041,1156,445,471]" country="Canada" name="Manitoba" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Manitoba</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1176,1269,445,471]" country="Canada" name="Ontario" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ontario</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1347,1436,445,471]" country="Canada" name="Quebec" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Québec</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McNamara, J." box="[158,374,485,511]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="201 - 205" refId="ref23391" refString="McNamara, J. (1991 c) Family Anobiidae: deathwatch beetles. In Bousquet, Y. (Ed.) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Agriculture Canada Publication 1861 / E. Ottawa, Ontario, pp. 201 - 205." type="book chapter" year="1991">McNamara 1991c</bibRefCitation>
). Frequent at ultraviolet lights (
<bibRefCitation author="Downie, N. M. &amp; Arnett, R. H., Jr." box="[741,1017,485,511]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref22003" refString="Downie, N. M. &amp; Arnett, R. H., Jr. (1996) The beetles of northeastern North America. Sandhill Crane Press, Gainesville, Florida. 1721 pp." type="book" year="1996">Downie &amp; Arnett 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Found boring in woodwork and in hardwoods and softwoods (
<bibRefCitation author="White, R. E." box="[472,616,525,551]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="529 - 70" refId="ref23969" refString="White, R. E. (1982) A catalogue of the Coleoptera of America north of Mexico, Family Anobiidae. United States Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service, Agricultural Handbook 529 - 70." type="book chapter" year="1982">White 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
